    <div class="articles">
      <div class="article">
        <img src="https://example.com/skate.jpg" alt="Skateboarding">
        <h2>Skateboarding: The Best of the Tracks</h2>
        <p> Discover the best tricks and how to prepare for the biggest challenges on the tracks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="article">

        <img src="app\assets\images\mega.png" alt="mega">
         

        <h2>Mega Ramp skateboarding</h2>
        <p>Mega Ramp skateboarding is one of the most extreme and thrilling forms of skateboarding, where skaters tackle gigantic ramps that can be over 20 meters high and 100 meters long. This massive structure allows athletes to reach incredible speeds and perform spectacular aerial maneuvers that often defy gravity..</p>

      </div>
      <div class="article">
        <img src="https://example.com/escalada.jpg" alt="Street">
        <h2>Street Skate: The Style Born on the Streets</h2>
        <p>Street Skate, or simply street, is one of the most popular forms of skateboarding and is deeply connected to urban culture. Originating on the streets and sidewalks of big cities, this style is characterized by the use of natural obstacles in the urban environment, such as stairs, handrails, benches, curbs and walls. Street skaters adapt these elements to create maneuvers and tricks that require technique, balance and creativity..</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

